Brutus: Brutus, the first consul, was killed in battle by Aruns, son of Tarquinius Superbus, 509 B.C. —Decius . . . filius . . . nepos: at the battle of Vesuvius in the war against the Latins, 340 B.C., P. Decius Mus offered his life as a voluntary sacrifice to propitiate the gods and win victory for the Romans. His son imitated his example at the battle of Sentinum, 295 B.C., in the war against the Samnites and Etruscans. The grandson is said to have met a like fate at the battle of Asculum, 279 B.C.,in the war against Pyrrhus,
